editorialSummary.text: Cavernous, futuristic nightspot with live DJs, VIP table service & private karaoke rooms.

originalText.text: Came here for a concert the other day to see PGONE and the space felt kinda small with everyone standing, people were smoking inside so not a fan of that. So hard getting out at the end too with people standing around and blocking the way. They didn't do a good job directing the crowd. Average experience for me.

originalText.text: Atmosphere spectacular. The seating is a loss opportunity to capitalize on the views. Not sure why they would seat 7 dudes in a circle booth. The seating arrangement was highly uncomfortable. We asked our first waitress for an additional chair she rolled her eyes and forgot about our request. We ask the guy who served the water and he immediately got us a chair which allowed us to seat comfortably. The lobster roll was mid at best. Literally three small lobster meat on the bun, which was blasphemy considering NY is known for some sick loaded lobster rolls. The waitress continued to be short with us. She was terrible in so many ways. I felt like I was ordering from Omarosa the horrid tv personality. But AMA took over for her for some reason and AMA was awesome! AMA has a great personality and answered all our questions. AMA had us try more drinks and food. $1000+ tab

originalText.text:
Standard midtown bar. Trouble is the dead eyed, sullen faced bartender girl at the main bar last night - I ordered one double tequila neat - paid $47 - why? Because she she added 20% gratuity without asking - could have easily added more myself by accident. Check your checks before you tip and sign at this spot folks!

Also I witnessed the staff  bodycheck a guest out of their way, (almost knocking him over) while breaking down the step and repeat and bringing in some seating. To add insult to injury: after pushing him, they yelled at him.

Some of the staff were lovely. So it's a mixed bag. Nice interior, decent sound.
